# SEO and Accessibility Requirements

## Meta Tags
Every page must include:
- `description` meta tag with unique, relevant content (150-160 characters)
- `keywords` meta tag with relevant keywords
- Proper page title format: "[Page Name] - Summerfield Consulting"

## Open Graph Tags
All pages must have:
- `og:title` - Format: "[Page Name] - Summerfield Consulting"
- `og:description` - Unique description (different from meta description)
- `og:image` - Path: "/logo.jpg"
- `og:url` - Format: "https://summerfieldconsulting.com/[path]"
- `og:type` - Value: "website"

## Accessibility Requirements
Every page must include:
1. Skip to main content link:

2. Proper ARIA attributes:
- `role="main"` on main content
- `role="banner"` on header
- `role="contentinfo"` on footer
- `role="navigation"` on nav elements
- `aria-current="page"` on active navigation items
- `aria-label` on interactive elements
- `aria-live` regions for dynamic content

3. Semantic HTML:
- Use proper heading hierarchy (h1-h6)
- Use semantic elements (main, header, footer, nav, etc.)
- Use lists for navigation items

## Content Guidelines
1. Page Titles:
- Home: "Summerfield Consulting"
- Services: "[Service Name] - Summerfield Consulting"

2. Meta Descriptions:
- Should be unique for each page
- Include main keywords naturally
- Be compelling and action-oriented
- Stay within 150-160 characters

3. Keywords:
- Include 5-8 relevant keywords
- Focus on service-specific terms
- Include variations of important terms

## Implementation Checklist
When creating new pages:
1. Copy meta tag structure from existing page
2. Update all meta content for new page
3. Ensure all ARIA attributes are properly set
4. Add skip-to-main-content link
5. Verify proper heading hierarchy
6. Test with screen reader
7. Validate Open Graph tags